						<summary>

						<p>Slab built into the wall of village <hi rend="italic">ghūḍe.</hi></p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">929 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>The record is damaged and incomplete. It registers a grant of 96 <hi rend="italic">mattar</hi> of land and six <hi rend="italic">gāṇa</hi> (oil-mills) to the god Nāgēśvara of Keṟeyūru probably by Nāga <hi rend="italic">gāvuṇḍa.</hi></p>						

						<p>It is dated Śaka 849 Sarvvadhāri, Phālguṇa Su. 7, Sunday, Rōhini-nakstra. It corresponds with 929 A.D., February 19. But the week day was Thursday. Nakshatra Rōhini was current.</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
